title: Rasheed Martin, Billy Cobb shine as Trinity crushes Lincoln
text:
Rasheed Martin, Billy Cobb shine as Trinity crushes Lincoln 
By The Times-Union Thu, Oct 22, 2015 @ 10:03 pm | updated Thu, Oct 22, 2015 @ 10:59 pm 

TRINITY CHRISTIAN 49 
TALLAHASSEE LINCOLN 18 
Rasheed Martin scored three touchdowns, including a 96-yard catch-and-run from a screen pass, in the Conquerors’ 49-18 rout at Tallahassee Lincoln (2-6). ... Trinity quarterback Billy Cobb completed 16 of 26 passes for 322 yards and four touchdowns... Dae’Quantae Showers opened the floodgates for Trinity Christian (8-0) with a 47-yard touchdown catch. ... Senior receiver Damien McGhee caught two touchdown passes and the Conquerors’ Jalin Buie also scored on a 60-yard rush. ... With just two games left, the Conquerors are closing in on their first unbeaten regular season since 2009. They can wrap up the District 2-3A title when they host Episcopal on Oct. 29. Trinity closes the regular season at home on Nov. 6 against Pensacola Pine Forest. Barring an upset, the Conquerors will host a Region 1-3A semifinal game on Nov. 13. ... Trinity has now won 16 consecutive games, with its last loss coming on Oct. 16, 2014 at IMG Academy.
